reporting-org.narrative: The federal government of the United States

description.narrative: Assist the Government of Botswana (GoB) to improve effective implementation of its anti-money laundering and countering the financing of terrorism (AML/CFT) regime. Proposed capacity building activities include (1) improving the operation of the Financial Intelligence Agency (FIA), Botswana’s financial intelligence unit (FIU); and (2) enhancing the ability of law enforcement and prosecution stakeholders to investigate and prosecute money laundering and underlying predicate crimes.. Assist the Government of Botswana (GoB) to improve effective implementation of its anti-money laundering and countering the financing of terrorism (AML/CFT) regime. Capacity building activities include (1) improving the operation of the Financial Intelligence Agency (FIA), Botswana’s financial intelligence unit (FIU); and (2) enhancing the ability of law enforcement and prosecution stakeholders to investigate and prosecute money laundering and underlying predicate crimes.

owner-org.narrative: The federal government of the United States

description.narrative: Botswana is one of the United States' strongest allies in Africa and offers a powerful model to the region and world of a stable, democratic African nation. However, while attempting to meet the pressing need to diversify its diamond-dependent economy, Botswana continues to struggle to address one of the world's highest rates of income inequality and the second highest HIV prevalence rate in the world. U.S. assistance supports management of the HIV/AIDS epidemic, including the epidemic's broader impact on women and vulnerable citizens. U.S. assistance also seeks to build a more robust military-to-military partnership with Botswana while encouraging its support for regional security.
